# AGENTS.md

## Project Identity

- Project: {project_name}
- Spec: {spec_path}

## Branching

- Use one branch per task with these prefixes: `feat/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`,
  `docs/`, `spike/`, `chore/`
- Never work directly on `{default_branch}`
- The engine handles merges after reviewer approval

## Commits

- Use conventional prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`,
  `chore:`
- Keep commits small and coherent

## Environment

- Use `./venv/bin/python` and `./venv/bin/pip`
- Never use system Python

## Testing

- Run `{test_command}` before marking work complete

## Documentation

- Create ADRs in `docs/adr/` for meaningful architectural decisions
- Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` when the codebase structure changes
  significantly
- Update `docs/ROADMAP.md` when completed work changes the next priorities
- Create `CHANGELOG.md` when the project matures enough that change tracking is
  useful

## Signals

Emit `FOREMAN_SIGNAL: {{...}}` lines when needed:

- `task_started`: use when you select work autonomously; include `title` and
  optionally `task_type`, `branch`, and `criteria`
- `task_created`: use when you discover follow-up work; include `title` and
  optionally `task_type`, `description`, and `criteria`
- `progress`: use for material progress updates; include `message`
- `blocker`: use when human help is required; include `message`

## Completion

- When the shipped developer role finishes, end with `{completion_marker}`
- Provide a structured completion summary before the marker

## Constraints

- Never merge to `{default_branch}`
- Never edit files under `{context_dir}/`
- Never bypass denied or approval-gated operations
